00:00:20.345 --> 00:00:24.470
OK, so negative space, so I want
to talk a little bit about what

00:00:24.470 --> 00:00:27.260
I mean when I say that word.

00:00:27.260 --> 00:00:31.430
Negative space, as it's
typically understood,

00:00:31.430 --> 00:00:36.980
is a formal or art term
that is the space between,

00:00:36.980 --> 00:00:42.500
under, around, inside an
object or subject of interest.

00:00:42.500 --> 00:00:46.640
It is the atmosphere, unseen
matter, the non-event.

00:00:46.640 --> 00:00:49.580
Positive space is
the subject object,

00:00:49.580 --> 00:00:53.420
the thing around which we orient
our understanding of what is,

00:00:53.420 --> 00:00:55.490
and thereby, what isn't.

00:00:55.490 --> 00:00:59.810
So this sets up a kind of binary
that I find really problematic,

00:00:59.810 --> 00:01:03.680
where you have this sort
of shapeless absence

00:01:03.680 --> 00:01:07.460
as the negative,
and the occupation,

00:01:07.460 --> 00:01:09.907
or defined space,
as the positive.

00:01:12.890 --> 00:01:15.560
As with any binary, I'm
interested in removing

00:01:15.560 --> 00:01:17.180
the primary.

00:01:17.180 --> 00:01:19.640
I don't think binaries are
inherently problematic.

00:01:19.640 --> 00:01:21.770
It's the imbalance of
power within a binary

00:01:21.770 --> 00:01:24.680
that I am always kind of
interested in undoing.

00:01:27.470 --> 00:01:31.520
So my reading on negative space
is that it has its own agency,

00:01:31.520 --> 00:01:32.570
that it is unfixed.

00:01:32.570 --> 00:01:35.240
It's dynamic, changeable,
and ultimately,

00:01:35.240 --> 00:01:37.460
free to form and reform.

00:01:37.460 --> 00:01:39.500
So I find negative space
to be really exciting.

00:01:39.500 --> 00:01:43.390
Because the positive
space is kind of stuck.

00:01:43.390 --> 00:01:46.160
And the negative space
is the thing that

00:01:46.160 --> 00:01:48.930
has the most potential, really.

00:01:48.930 --> 00:01:52.010
So this is the reason
it's very hard for me

00:01:52.010 --> 00:01:53.840
to talk about this
work in under an hour.

